---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for QuizNiva."
  currentPath="/privacy-policy"
>
  <section class="page-intro section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: May 26, 2026</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section prose prose--standalone">
    <h2>Information QuizNiva Stores</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva does not require an account and does not ask visitors to create a profile. Quiz progress, best scores, attempts, visited lessons, theme preference, and the last visited topic may be stored in your own browser using localStorage. This information stays on your device unless you clear your browser data.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
    <p>
      If you email QuizNiva, we receive the email address and message content you choose to send. We use that information to reply, review corrections, handle suggestions, and improve the site. Do not send passwords, payment details, or sensitive personal information through email.
    </p>

    <h2>Advertising, Cookies, And Consent</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva may use Google AdSense to show advertising. Advertising partners may use cookies, local storage, device identifiers, or similar technologies to deliver ads, limit repetition, measure performance, and help prevent abuse. The site displays a privacy choice prompt so visitors can accept or reject non-essential advertising requests.
    </p>
    <p>
      Essential browser storage for quiz progress and theme preference is used to make the study experience work. Advertising storage is optional. If you reject advertising cookies, the site should still remain available for reading lessons and taking quizzes.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva does not use third-party analytics tracking scripts. Hosting and security providers may process standard server request data such as IP address, browser type, requested URL, and timestamp to deliver the site, protect against abuse, and maintain reliable service.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>
      Some pages link to external educational resources, such as official documentation or reference material. Those third-party websites have their own privacy policies and may collect information according to their own terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Children And Students</h2>
    <p>
      QuizNiva is an educational site, but it is not intended to collect personal information from children. Students should use the site with guidance from a parent, guardian, or teacher when required by local rules.
    </p>

    <h2>Managing Data</h2>
    <p>
      You can clear QuizNiva progress, cookie choices, and theme preference by clearing site data in your browser settings. You can also change browser settings to block or delete cookies.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy questions, contact the site owner at
      <a class="text-link" href="mailto:contact@quizniva.in">contact@quizniva.in</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
